---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.svelte'
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Peter Hou" description="About Peter Hou">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="content">
        <p>Hi, I'm <strong>Peter Hou</strong>. You found it!</p>
        <details class="collapsible">
          <summary>This site</summary>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>I'm so happy to have landed this version of my homepage in 2026 — the third major iteration since the first was born in 2017, with the second following in 2023. With the help of AI, it has never felt so good to be a builder ever. Ideas become real so fast in this era.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="collapsible">
          <summary>Travel</summary>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>I travel when I get the chance — and that's quite a lot. I love losing myself in different cultures and chasing landscapes that take my breath away.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="collapsible">
          <summary>Sports</summary>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>I love sports (and I'm really not a gym person in any way). I'd much rather be out on the field: sweating through a game, sprinting to score, leaping to defend, and making full use of agility and movement. I love the competition of speed and strength, the intensity, and the feeling of being fully immersed in play. My sport of choice shifts over the years. Basketball, badminton, ultimate frisbee, baseball, American football, and more — each has been my favorite at one point or another. These days I primarily play frisbee and flag football, and I have no idea when my focus will shift again.</p>
            <p>In 2025, I happened to try softball for the first time with a group of friends — and quickly developed an interest in the game. I started watching MLB, where I got to witness the Seattle Mariners make their first ALCS appearance since 2001.</p>
            <p>It was also in 2025 that I became deeply invested in the NFL. Earlier that year, I watched the Eagles' win over the Chiefs, who had just won two straight Super Bowls in 2023 and 2024. From there I followed most of the games throughout the new season. The speed and strength, the strategy and physicality, the battle at the line of scrimmage, the beautiful connection between quarterback and receiver — every play drew me further in. I only wish I'd gotten into this sport sooner. I feel so fortunate, as a new fan, to have watched the Seattle Seahawks' legendary run all season long and witnessed their big win in the Super Bowl.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="collapsible">
          <summary>Music</summary>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>I've been drawn to musical instruments since I was young, and I've always admired people who can perform — whether solo or as part of a band. Yet for a long time, I rarely had the chance to seriously learn or develop those skills myself.</p>
            <p>I bought my first guitar in college and started learning from scratch. Over the years I picked up the basics, but eventually drifted away from it, partly because I struggled to stay motivated. Recently, though, I've returned to it — rebuilding old habits while slowly developing new skills.</p>
            <p>At the end of 2023, I ended up getting a secondhand piano in remarkably good condition given its age. Since then, I've been teaching myself with <em>Alfred's Adult All-in-One Piano Course</em>, which I've found to be an excellent resource. Progress has not always been steady — sometimes life leaves little room for practice — but I genuinely enjoy the process. It took me about a year to complete Book 1, and I'm now working through the final pieces of Book 2.</p>
            <p>Unlike sports, where improvement often came more naturally to me, music has been a humbling experience. The time and effort are there, but progress feels gradual, and I still haven't reached the level I once imagined for myself. Perhaps I simply need more patience. Perhaps guidance from a good teacher would help. Either way, I hope that somewhere down the road, a breakthrough is waiting.</p>
            <p>I used to sing pop songs as well, though these days I rarely do.</p>

          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="collapsible">
          <summary>Other hobbies</summary>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>Beyond what I've shared above, I have some other casual hobbies.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <p>I currently live on Mercer Island, nestled in Lake Washington just east of downtown Seattle.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <div class="contact">
        <h2>Leave Me a Message</h2>
        <ContactForm client:load />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .collapsible {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .collapsible summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nav-color);
    list-style: none;
  }

  .collapsible summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .collapsible summary::before {
    content: '▸';
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .collapsible[open] summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .collapsible-body {
    padding: 0 1rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .contact h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--nav-color);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
</style>
